		<script type="application/ld+json" class="mv-create-json-ld mv-create-json-ld-recipe">{"@context":"http:\/\/schema.org","@type":"Recipe","name":"Kohlrabi Soup with Kohlrabi Greens","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Carla Cardello"},"datePublished":"2018-11-15","recipeYield":4,"description":"Not sure what to do with kohlrabi leaves? Make this beautifully orange Kohlrabi Soup with kohlrabi greens, sweet potato, and carrots! It\u2019s a gluten free vegan soup, perfect for when you want a meatless meal.","image":["https:\/\/www.chocolatemoosey.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2011\/01\/Kohlrabi-Soup-with-Kohlrabi-Greens-recipe-photo-0001-320x320.jpg","https:\/\/www.chocolatemoosey.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2011\/01\/Kohlrabi-Soup-with-Kohlrabi-Greens-recipe-photo-0001-480x360.jpg","https:\/\/www.chocolatemoosey.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2011\/01\/Kohlrabi-Soup-with-Kohlrabi-Greens-recipe-photo-0001.jpg","https:\/\/www.chocolatemoosey.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2011\/01\/Kohlrabi-Soup-with-Kohlrabi-Greens-recipe-photo-0001-480x270.jpg"],"recipeCategory":"Soups + Stews","recipeCuisine":"American","prepTime":"PT30M","cookTime":"PT1H","performTime":"PT1H","totalTime":"PT1H30M","recipeIngredient":["1 tablespoon olive oil","    Salt (preferably kosher), to taste","    1\/4 cup diced white or yellow onion","    1 large carrot, peeled and diced","    1 clove garlic, minced","    5 cups vegetable broth\/stock","    1 pound kohlrabi, bulbs peeled and diced and leaves chopped","    1 small sweet potato, peeled and diced (roughly 8 ounces)","    1 tablespoon lemon juice"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"In a Dutch oven or large pot, add the oil. Once hot, add the onion, carrot, and a big pinch of salt. Cook until they start to soften and brown, about 3-5 minutes. Add the garlic and cook 1 minute.","position":1,"name":"In a Dutch oven or large pot, add...","url":"https:\/\/www.chocolatemoosey.com\/hungarian-kohlrabi-soup-kalarabeleves\/#mv_create_95_1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add 1 + 1\/2 cups broth and bring to a boil. Cook until carrots are softened, about 8-10 minutes.","position":2,"name":"Add 1 + 1\/2 cups broth and bring...","url":"https:\/\/www.chocolatemoosey.com\/hungarian-kohlrabi-soup-kalarabeleves\/#mv_create_95_2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Transfer mixture to a blender and blend until smooth. There should be enough broth but if it's too thick to blend, you can add a little more.","position":3,"name":"Transfer mixture to a blender and blend until...","url":"https:\/\/www.chocolatemoosey.com\/hungarian-kohlrabi-soup-kalarabeleves\/#mv_create_95_3"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Pour the carrot puree back into the Dutch oven. Add the remaining 3 + 1\/2 cups broth then bring to a boil.","position":4,"name":"Pour the carrot puree back into the Dutch...","url":"https:\/\/www.chocolatemoosey.com\/hungarian-kohlrabi-soup-kalarabeleves\/#mv_create_95_4"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Once boiling, add the kohlrabi bulbs, sweet potato, and a big pinch of salt. Cook until fork tender, about 15 minutes.You should have enough broth, but if your vegetable amounts are bigger than indicated, it's possible you may need to add more as the vegetables will absorb the broth.","position":5,"name":"Once boiling, add the kohlrabi bulbs, sweet potato,...","url":"https:\/\/www.chocolatemoosey.com\/hungarian-kohlrabi-soup-kalarabeleves\/#mv_create_95_5"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add kohlrabi leaves and cook 3-5 minutes until the leaves are softened. Add lemon juice then taste and adjust for salt.","position":6,"name":"Add kohlrabi leaves and cook 3-5 minutes until...","url":"https:\/\/www.chocolatemoosey.com\/hungarian-kohlrabi-soup-kalarabeleves\/#mv_create_95_6"}],"keywords":"kohlrabi soup","suitableForDiet":"VeganDiet","aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":4.4,"reviewCount":"88"},"url":"https:\/\/www.chocolatemoosey.com\/hungarian-kohlrabi-soup-kalarabeleves\/"}</script><meta name="hubbub-info" description="Hubbub 1.34.7"><meta name="pinterest-rich-pin" content="false" />		<style type="text/css" id="wp-custom-css">
