                <a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-491714" data-commentid="491714" data-postid="1910" data-belowelement="comment-491714" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Bryna" aria-label="Reply to Bryna">Reply</a>                            </div><!-- .comment-meta -->
			
			<p>Made it exactly as written, really good! Would consider adding chicken next time as mentioned above to make the macros more balanced, but it was delicious as written. May have to check out that cookbook where you got the inspiration from. Thanks!</p>

